The paper discusses the intersection of photonics and neuromorphic computing, which involves the design and implementation of hardware that mimics the behavior of biological neurons and synapses. This topic falls under several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.OH (Other Computer Science). The paper's focus on hardware design and performance metrics suggests that cs.ET and cs.IT are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.NE and cs.AI, while cs.OH is a catch-all category that could apply to any interdisciplinary work.
